The paper discusses a new decoding paradigm for error correction codes in communication channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of large state spaces and state transition procedures also involves concepts from systems and control theory (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the potential performance of the proposed method compared to existing error correction codes, which is a topic related to systems and control theory (cs.SY).
